<% content_for :title do %>
  Site Reliability Engineering at Manulife
<% end %>
<div style="height: 100px;"></div>
<div class="mx-5 text-light">
  <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mx-0 mb-5">
    <div class="col-auto text-center">
      <%= image_tag("manulife_logo.jpg", alt: "Manulife", height: 80) %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-auto ps-4">
      <p class="fw-bold font-monospace my-0" style="font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3rem);">Cloud Platforms Engineer</p>
      <p class="text-opacity-75 font-monospace my-0" style="font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);">May 2023 &ndash; August 2023 &middot; Toronto, ON</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="height: 40px;"></div>
  <div class="row mx-0 justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-lg-9 col-xxl-8">
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        During my Cloud Platforms Engineering internship at Manulife, I worked within the DevPlat Reliability
        DevOps team to support and improve cloud infrastructure across Manulife ETS. A key deliverable was
        automating the migration of 10% of all API endpoints from Apigee to Microsoft API Management using
        Node.js, which improved request latency by 15% and moved the organization closer to a modernized
        API gateway strategy.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        I designed and launched a React dashboard to service 100+ project managers awaiting approval on internal
        corporate request tickets, cutting ticket wait times by 83% and consolidating previously fragmented
        approval workflows into a single interface. This significantly reduced bottlenecks that had been slowing
        cross-team delivery.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        On the observability side, I configured 10 New Relic synthetic monitors and integrated them with the
        MoogSoft AIOps alert system to proactively surface infrastructure anomalies before they impacted
        end users. I also supported day-to-day DevOps reliability by resolving PaaS incidents and optimizing
        Docker- and Azure-based CI/CD pipelines.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div style="height: 150px;"></div>